<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1950,2013]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1437,151,501]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="328" pageId="15" pageNumber="327">
Material examined: 
<collectingCountry box="[376,460,1951,1977]" name="Turkey" pageId="15" pageNumber="327">Turkey</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[471,553,1951,1977]" country="Turkey" name="Mersin" pageId="15" pageNumber="327">Mersin</collectingRegion>
, Anamur, 
<date box="[667,796,1950,1977]" pageId="15" pageNumber="327" value="2020-06-15">15.06.2020</date>
, 
<specimenCount box="[807,851,1951,1977]" pageId="15" pageNumber="327" type="male">1 ♂</specimenCount>
, Ö. Koçak leg., B. Çerçi det. (BCIT) Comments: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1874" box="[335,540,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Tempyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="327" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biguttula">
<emphasis box="[335,540,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="327">Tempyra biguttula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a Nearctic species originally described from 
<collectingRegion box="[1074,1142,1987,2013]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="15" pageNumber="327">Texas</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1153,1207,1987,2013]" name="United States of America" pageId="15" pageNumber="327">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stal, C." box="[1223,1335,1986,2013]" pageId="15" pageNumber="327" pagination="43 - 59" refId="ref10782" refString="Stal, C. (1874) Genera Tingitidarum Europae disposuit. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, 31 (3), 43 - 59." type="journal article" year="1874">Stål 1874</bibRefCitation>
). Later it was found from several southern and northern states of 
<collectingCountry box="[784,843,151,177]" name="United States of America" pageId="16" pageNumber="328">USA</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[855,939,151,177]" country="United States of America" name="Hawaii" pageId="16" pageNumber="328">Hawaii</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[951,1039,151,177]" name="Mexico" pageId="16" pageNumber="328">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1051,1113,151,177]" name="Cuba" pageId="16" pageNumber="328">Cuba</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1125,1218,151,177]" name="Jamaica" pageId="16" pageNumber="328">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
, Galápagos Islands and 
<collectingCountry box="[198,309,187,213]" name="Argentina" pageId="16" pageNumber="328">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kirkaldy, G. W." box="[324,492,187,213]" pageId="16" pageNumber="328" pagination="118 - 123" refId="ref9760" refString="Kirkaldy, G. W. (1910) Further notes on Hemiptera chiefly Hawaiian. Proceedings of the Hawaiian Entomological Society, 2 (3), 118 - 123." type="journal article" year="1910">Kirkaldy 1910</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Slater, J. A." box="[504,642,187,213]" pageId="16" pageNumber="328" refId="ref10709" refString="Slater, J. A. (1964) A Catalogue of the Lygaeidae of the world. 2 Vols. University of Connecticut, Storrs, Connecticut, 1668 pp." type="book" year="1964">Slater, 1964</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Froeschner, R. C." box="[654,845,186,213]" pageId="16" pageNumber="328" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref9258" refString="Froeschner, R. C. (1985) Synopsis of the Heteroptera or True Bugs of the Galapagos Islands. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 407, i - iii + 1 - 84. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.407" type="journal article" year="1985">Froeschner 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Baranowski, R. M. &amp; Slater, J. A." box="[858,1160,186,213]" pageId="16" pageNumber="328" pagination="1 - 266" refId="ref8709" refString="Baranowski, R. M. &amp; Slater, J. A. (2005) The Lygaeidae of the West Indies. University of Florida, Institute of Food and Agricultural Sciences. Florida Agricultural Experimental Station Bulletin, 402, 1 - 266." type="journal article" year="2005">Baranowski &amp; Slater 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Carpintero, D. L. &amp; Dellape, P. M. &amp; Melo, M. C." box="[1172,1425,187,214]" pageId="16" pageNumber="328" pagination="1 - 22" refId="ref8806" refString="Carpintero, D. L., Dellape, P. M. &amp; Melo, M. C. (2006) New Records of Heteroptera (Hemiptera) from Argentina. Zootaxa, 1129, 1 - 22. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1129.1.1" type="journal article" year="2006">
Carpintero 
<emphasis box="[1300,1357,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="328">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
). More recently, in 2011, this species was introduced to 
<collectingCountry box="[775,839,223,249]" name="Spain" pageId="16" pageNumber="328">Spain</collectingCountry>
and started to spread along the coastline of Western Mediterranean Region as an invasive alien species. It was recorded from several localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[1202,1266,259,285]" name="Spain" pageId="16" pageNumber="328">Spain</collectingCountry>
(Baena &amp; Torres 2012), 
<collectingCountry box="[270,368,295,321]" name="Portugal" pageId="16" pageNumber="328">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[379,455,295,321]" name="France" pageId="16" pageNumber="328">France</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Maurel, J. P. &amp; Porteneuve, J. J." box="[470,780,295,321]" pageId="16" pageNumber="328" pagination="47 - 50" refId="ref10239" refString="Maurel, J. P. &amp; Porteneuve, J. J. (2018) Tempyra biguttula Stal, 1874 une nouvelle punaise invasive decouverte en Occitanie (Heteroptera; Lygaeidae; Rhyparochrominae). Carnetes Natures, 5, 47 - 50." type="journal article" year="2018">Maurel &amp; Porteneuve 2018</bibRefCitation>
) and Sardinia (
<bibRefCitation author="Rattu, A. &amp; Dioli, P." box="[950,1174,295,321]" pageId="16" pageNumber="328" pagination="315 - 320" refId="ref10432" refString="Rattu, A. &amp; Dioli, P. (2018) Tempyra biguttula Stal, 1874, una specie esotica di origine americana nuova per l'Italia (Hemipterta: Rhyparochromidae). Revista Gaditana de Entomologia, 9 (1), 315 - 320." type="journal article" year="2018">Rattu &amp; Dioli 2018</bibRefCitation>
). This new record from 
<collectingRegion box="[151,233,331,357]" country="Turkey" name="Mersin" pageId="16" pageNumber="328">Mersin</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[243,323,331,357]" name="Turkey" pageId="16" pageNumber="328">Turkey</collectingCountry>
greatly enlarges the known distribution of this species in the Palaearctic Region from West Mediterranean to the East Mediterranean (
<figureCitation box="[541,619,367,393]" captionStart="MAP 2" captionStartId="17.[151,207,1634,1658]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,968,1611]" captionTargetId="figure-81@17.[151,1436,968,1611]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="MAP 2. Distribution of Tempyra biguttula Stål, 1874 in the Palaearctic Region. Circles mark previous records, star marks the new record from Turkey." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4666487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4666487/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="328">Map 2</figureCitation>
). Although the biology and ecology of this species is almost completely unknown, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rattu, A. &amp; Dioli, P." box="[270,508,403,429]" pageId="16" pageNumber="328" pagination="315 - 320" refId="ref10432" refString="Rattu, A. &amp; Dioli, P. (2018) Tempyra biguttula Stal, 1874, una specie esotica di origine americana nuova per l'Italia (Hemipterta: Rhyparochromidae). Revista Gaditana de Entomologia, 9 (1), 315 - 320." type="journal article" year="2018">Rattu &amp; Dioli (2018)</bibRefCitation>
put the argument forward, based on previous observations in Europe, that it could take refuge in occasional shelters where there were seeds of different plants, particularly 
<taxonomicName box="[1145,1249,439,465]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="16" pageNumber="328" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
seeds and easily adapt to the plant species available in the newly colonized territories.
</paragraph>
